To run any of the code provided by this library, you must have PHP5.3+ installed. After that,
run the tests to see what packages you still need to install to get everything working.

we assume the user who runs the test can connect to the database over 127.0.0.1 with no password
for mysql and postgres.

Check below for the relevant packages we have installed on our test machines.

Tested on Centos 5 x86_64 GNU/Linux with the following packages installed:

beanstalkd.x86_64                        1.4.6-2.el5
